{{Infobox power station | name = Aggreko Power Station | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Sri Lanka | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|09|44|25|N|80|02|06|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = Sri Lanka | location = [[Jaffna]] | status = Decommissioned | construction_began = | commissioned = 1 October 2003 | decommissioned = 31 December 2012 | cost = | owner = | operator = [[Aggreko]] | th_fuel_primary = [[Fuel oil]] | th_fuel_secondary = | th_fuel_tertiary = | th_technology = | th_feed_mine = | th_cogeneration = | th_combined_cycle = | th_cooling_source = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_thermal_capacity = | ps_electrical_capacity = {{Nowrap|20 [[Megawatt|MW]]}} | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_storage_hours = | ps_annual_generation = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Aggreko Power Station''' was a temporary 20-[[megawatt]] [[fuel oil]]-fired power station which was commissioned in October 2003 after [[Aggreko]], the world's largest [[temporary power generation]] company, won an open bid offered by the [[Ceylon Electricity Board]] to overcome the Sri Lanka energy crisis faced in the 1990s to early 2000s. It was later decommissioned on 31 December 2012. Prior to decommissioning, Aggreko sold electricity to the [[Ceylon Electricity Board]] at a rate of {{Nowrap|[[Sri Lankan Rupee|Rs.]] 26 per [[KWh]]}}.<ref>{{cite news|last1=R. Satyapalan|first1=Franklin|title=Uninterrupted power supply to Jaffna soon: Emergency power supplier Aggreko’s contract terminated|url=http://www.island.lk/index.php?page_cat=article-details&page=article-details&code_title=70680|accessdate=8 November 2015|publisher=[[The Island (Sri Lanka)|The Island]]|date=18 January 2013}}</ref><ref name=DailyNews2003>{{cite news|last1=Sirimane|first1=Shirajiv|title=Aggreko invests $50m on Jaffna power plant|url=http://archives.dailynews.lk/2003/07/22/bus04.html|accessdate=8 November 2015|publisher=[[Daily News (Sri Lanka)|Daily News]]|date=22 July 2003}}</ref> {{Clear}}
